review_blob: A great example of good lager. In a great form - normal lager with freshly added younger beer. It has higher carbonation with a great drinkability. Aroma is hoppy fresh. Hops & yeast dominates the taste, with a little bit signs of sour aftertaste. One of my favorites.

Really nothing special...
Quite a good drinkability, but almost no bitterness and a little bit of a sour aftertaste...

Well, this one is a difficult rating. Because its a micro brew, the quality differs and by that, I mean A LOT. Sometimes its really dissapointing beer, sometimes its really good.
So, I wish you luck with this one.

A Czech classic.
When its tapped in a good pub, its still a really good beer. But a lot of Czech pubs tappes it with much less care then it deserves:-(
Hoppy aroma, nice carbonation and a good drinkability.
Due to lower alcohol content, one can survive even ten pieces without a significant hangover:-)

Nice roasty aroma, really dark color, chocolate tones in taste with a low bitterness. Full body with oily consistency. Dangerously good drinkability, despite high alcohol content. Quite a good piece, for a mass produced beer.

Nothing special, quite drinkable with dinner. 
With quite a poor foam, grainy aroma, and a very low bitterness.
But seems a bit better than a mass produced polish lagers....
